name: State Cinema 6/Stefano's Pizza
directions: There are three gender neutral bathrooms in the building, all on the first floor - if you are disabled there is an elevator at the back of the cinema by the arcade that you can use. Two bathrooms are at the Stefano's street entrance - they are on the landing up the stairs from the street, and you don't have to go into the cinema or Stefano's to use them. The third is by the elevator, there's a windy bit of corridor leading to one of the smaller cinemas, and the bathroom is also along that corridor.

name: Columbus Museum of Art
directions: The very back hallway on the first floor. It's slightly below ground level, and there are stairs and an elevator to get to them.
comment: The CMA has a family restroom and a single stall restroom. You have to pay to get into the museum, and I don't expect someone to pay just to use the bathroom. But the CMA is a safe place that is very accepting of all people, and there are several elevators to make the whole building accessible. The museum has tons of great artwork and activities, and is an awesome place all around. So if you're ever visiting Columbus, make it a place to visit!
